+# 0115 — Context exploration planner
+
+0115 implements the first minimal planner after the 0114-r2 context variation
+core contract.
+
+context variability is the project center.
+
+The planner turns a `ContextVariationObjective into a bounded
+ContextExplorationPlan`. It is deterministic, reference-only, and side-effect
+free. It prepares context trajectories that handlers can later execute, but it
+never calls SQL, Qdrant, OpenVINO, LLM, GitHub, EventBus, or RouteRuntimeManager
+directly.
+
+## Operational shape
+
+```text
+ContextVariationObjective
+-> ContextExplorationPlanner
+-> ContextVariationAxis[]
+-> ContextVariantCandidate[]
+-> ContextTrajectory[]
+-> ContextExplorationPlan
+```
+
+The default trajectory skeleton is:
+
+```text
+SQL hydrate -> OpenVINO embed -> Qdrant recall -> SQL re-hydrate -> specialist note
+```
+
+This is only a set of `capability_hint` strings and typed refs. Real backends are
+future adapters behind handlers.
+
+## Scheduler role
+
+Scheduler orchestrates context exploration jobs; it does not build variants itself.
+
+The Scheduler can carry the resulting plan or a command that points to it, but
+`Scheduler.run()` does not import, construct, or execute SQL/Qdrant/OpenVINO/LLM
+logic.
+
+## Why this is not the rejected capability/security direction
+
+0115 is not a security/capability envelope. It is a context planner. Policy,
+zone, and admission remain guardrails. The objective remains fast solution
+production through bounded context variation.
+
+## Guardrails
+
+- No MVTC runtime in 0115.
+- No SQL/Qdrant/OpenVINO/LLM runtime import.
+- No new EventType.
+- No Scheduler.run() modification.
+- No Dispatcher / PriorityQueue / PolicyEngine / EventBus modification.
+- EventBus observation only.
+- Route mmap/eventfd remains data plane, not EventBus.
+- Payloads remain typed references, not embedded heavy content.
+- Standard library only.
+
+## Code rule review
+
+```text
+code_rule_review: done
+code_rule_update_required: false
+code_rule_reason: planner is a pure use-case/contract layer; concrete backends remain behind future adapters and handlers.
+live_path_status: transition
+live_path_uses_real_backend: n/a
+context_contract_version: missipy.context.v1
+context_contract_changed: true
+search_commands_bounded: true
+```
